[[Image:3VOOR12 logo.svg|150px|right|thumb|3VOOR12 Logo]]
'''3VOOR12''' is a [[multimedia]] platform of the [[Netherlands Public Broadcasting]] [[VPRO]] for [[alternative pop]].

3VOOR12 had 2 digital television channels (a [[videoclip|clip]]-channel and a [[concert]]-channel), different radio channels ranging from [[Punk rock|punk]], Roots and [[Alternative rock]] to [[Heavy metal music|metal]]), radio programs on [[3FM]], a [[website]] and a weekly live event (Club 3VOOR12). Also 3VOOR12 is present at several festivals ([[Noorderslag]], [[A Campingflight to Lowlands Paradise|Lowlands]], [[Motel Mozaïque]], [[Pinkpop]]). 3VOOR12 has been awarded several times. Among the awards are the UPC Digital Award, the Pritchett-award, the [[BNN (Dutch broadcaster)|BNN]] Rookie-Award and the Gouden Pixel.

Similar in approach to the ''[[In a Van Sessions]]'' and [[the Take-Away Shows]] the platform presents live performances of many touring artists recorded in elevators and other small rooms in the [[Netherlands]] under the umbrella name Behind Closed Doors<ref>[http://3voor12.vpro.nl/dossiers/dossier/21200079] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081118175521/http://3voor12.vpro.nl/dossiers/dossier/21200079 |date=November 18, 2008 }}</ref> These videos are presented on their website as well as an official 3VOOR12 [[YouTube]] account.

==Radio==
On radio 3VOOR12 broadcasts almost every day between 21:00-24:00. The programs are: Club 3VOOR12 ([[Eric Corton]], live music), Whitenoise ([[Dave Clarke (techno DJ)|Dave Clarke]], techno music), both on Dutch radio station [[3FM]].

