{{Infobox Bilateral relations|Burkina Faso-Denmark|Burkina Faso|Denmark}}

'''Burkina Faso–Denmark relations''' refers to the [[bilateralism|current and historical relationship]] between [[Burkina Faso]] and [[Denmark]]. Burkina Faso has an embassy in [[Copenhagen]], and Denmark has an embassy in [[Ouagadougou]].<ref>[http://www.ambaburkina.dk/intro.html Burkina Faso embassy in Copenhagen]</ref><ref>[http://www.ambouagadougou.um.dk/da/ Danish embassy in Ouagadougou &] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100916233029/http://www.ambouagadougou.um.dk/da/ |date=September 16, 2010 }} {{fr icon}} {{da icon}}</ref>

==Assistance==
Burkina Faso has, since 1973, been in a development cooperation with Denmark, and a programme country since 1993. Assistance for Burkina Faso was 233 million DKK in 2010; in 2013, Denmark assisted with 250 million [[Danish krone|DKK]].<ref>[http://www.ft.dk/samling/20101/almdel/uru/bilag/52/928712.pdf History between Burkina Faso and Denmark]</ref>

Denmark's main support is towards poverty reduction, through the Danish and Burkinabe Development Cooperation.<ref>[http://www.netpublikationer.dk/um/7647/pdf/87-7667-646-3.pdf Burkina Faso - Denmark Partnership] {{da icon}}</ref> Denmark also has an agriculture programme in Burkina Faso.<ref>[http://www.netpublikationer.dk/um/9115/html/entire_publication.htm#Section11.5 Danish assistance with Agriculture]</ref>

Several agreements have been signed between Denmark and Burkina Faso.<ref>[https://www.un-ilibrary.org/united-nations/treaty-series-1719_ea4db2ed-en-fr Exchange of letters constituting an agreement concerning support for the Pan African festival of cinema and television at Ouagadougou]</ref><ref>[https://www.un-ilibrary.org/international-law-and-justice/treaty-series-1690_2ce32f0a-en-fr Exchange of letters constituting an agreement concerning assistance for the process of democratization in Burkina Faso. Copenhagen, 22 May and 9 June 1992]</ref>

