[[File:Razglednica celjskega narodnega doma 1906.jpg|thumb|1906 postcard of Celje National Hall]]
'''Celje National Hall''' ({{lang-sl|Narodni dom}}) is a city hall in [[Celje]], a town in central-eastern [[Slovenia]]. It was built between 1895 and 1896 and today hosts the seat of a township. It was designed by the Czech [[architect]]s [[Jan Vladimír Hráský]] and {{Interlanguage link multi|Jan Vejrych|cs}} and was a multimodal building. Such [[national hall]]s were typical of the [[Slovene Lands]] of the period.

