{{Unreferenced|date=December 2006}}
The '''corridinho''' is a form of [[Portugal|Portuguese]] dance, namely in the [[Algarve]]. It is [[dance]]d with the pairs always embraced, forming a circle, girls inside and the boys outside the circle. By rotating the circle the pairs evolve side by side. At a certain time, when the music as a stronger beat, their feet hit the floor more intensely, stopping the rotation, to resume afterwards. Further away in the dance, the pairs embraced [[waltz]] by spinning in the same place. Next the circle starts rotating again always for the right side. It is a very traditional dance in Portugal that Portuguese people like doing.  Besides, you also see people enjoying the dance in the past Portuguese empire states like [[Goa]], [[Daman and Diu]], [[Dadra and Nagar Haveli]], small part of [[Ceylon]] (Sri Lanka) and [[Macau]] (China).

