{{unreferenced|date=December 2012}}

'''Act 1696''', or the '''Flag Act''', (Philippine Commission Act № 1696, August 23, 1907) is an act of the [[Philippine Commission]] that outlawed the display of [[Katipunan]] flags, banners, emblems, or devices in the [[American Colonial Period (Philippines)|American-controlled]] [[Insular Government|Philippine Islands]]. Both the current national anthem, ''[[Lupang Hinirang]]'', and the present-day [[Flag of the Philippines]], were covered by this ban.

The Flag Act was repealed by the [[Philippine Legislature]] in 1919.

