'''International Society of Addiction Medicine''' ('''ISAM'''), created in 1999, is an [[organization]] constituted of professional [[medical practitioners]], [[physicians]] and [[clinicians]] from 93 countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.isamweb.org/|title=ISAM}}</ref> ISAM as its mission has developed activities to bridge evidence with International practice.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://international.drugabuse.gov/meetings/abstractdatabase/result/fn%3D%2526amp%3Bln%3D%2526amp%3Bsub%3D%2526amp%3Byr%3D0%2526amp%3Bcat%3D0%2526amp%3Bco%3D0%2526amp%3Breg%3D0%2526amp%3Bid%3D1007/|title=ISAM bridging medical evidences}}</ref> ISAM organizes various [[Academic conference|conference]]s across the [[world]] related to [[addiction medicine]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.alcohol.org.nz/events/international-society-addiction-medicine-isam-2013-annual-meeting-managing-addiction-through-/|title=Conference Ref 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.ncme.ca/calendar/index.php?eID=10144/|title=Conference Ref}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://choopersguide.com/event/international-society-of-addiction-medicine-isam-addiction-conferences.html/|title= International Conference}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://cicg.ch/en/events/isam-2012/|title= Conference 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://triweb.tresearch.org/index.php/ai1ec_event/international-society-of-addiction-medicine-isam-annual-meeting/?instance_id=/|title= Annual Meeting}}</ref> The International Society of Addiction Medicine aims in transmitting [[knowledge]] of [[addiction]] that it is a treatable [[disease]], enhancing the credibility of [[physicians]] involved in treatment and to develop educational activities and [[consensus]] guidelines.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.bettyfordinstitute.org/publications/sci-mat/sci-mat-education/international-certification-of-addiction-medicine.php/|title= ISAM aim}}</ref>
