[[File:Map Prey Veng Province.png|thumb|300px|Roads in [[Prey Veng Province]].]]
'''National Road No. 8''' (10008) is one of the national [[highway]]s of [[Cambodia]].  The {{convert|90|km|abbr=on}} road is located in [[Prey Veng Province]] of southeastern Cambodia. 

It begins at the junction with [[National Highway 6 (Cambodia)|National Highway 6A]]. Immediately after it crosses the [[Mekong River]] on the [[Prek Tamak Bridge]], it turns east to the village of Amphil near the border with [[Vietnam]]. It ends at the junction with [[National Highway 7 (Cambodia)|National Highway 7]].<ref>Total Road Atlas of Cambodia 2006, 3rd edition, Total Cambodge, Phnom Penh, Cambodia</ref>

