{{Infobox bridge | name = Noefefan Bridge | native_name = Ponte Noefefan iha Tono | native_name_lang = Tetum language | image = | caption = | coordinates = {{Coord|display=inline,title|format=dms}} | crosses = [[Tono River]] | design = | material = concrete, steel | material1 = | material2 = | length = 380 m<ref name="tatoli"/> | width = | height = 20 m | depth = | towpath = | mainspan = | number_spans = 3 | piers_in_water = 2 | clearance_above = | clearance_below = | lanes = 2 | architect = | designer = | contracted_designer = | engineering = | builder = | fabricator = | begin = April 2015<ref name="tatoli"/> | complete = | cost = US$ 17.5 million<ref name="tatoli">[http://www.tatoli.tl/2017/06/ponte-noefefan-konstrui-ho-orsamentu-miloens-175/ Ponte Noefefan Konstrui ho Orsamentu Miloens $17,5] (in Tetum)</ref> | open = | inaugurated = 10 June 2017 | map_type = East Timor | map_relief = yes }} The '''Noefefan Bridge''' is a bridge over the [[Tono River]], in [[Oecusse]], [[East Timor]]. It was inaugurated on 10th June 2017 by the president of Timor-Leste, [[Francisco Guterres]].<ref name="zeesm">[https://www.zeesm.tl/opened-noefefan-bridge-tono/ Noefefan Bridge inaugurated]</ref>
The 3-arched bridge —which is 380 meters long and 20 meters high— connects [[Citrana]], [[Passabe]] and other isolated regions west of the Tono River to the regional capital of [[Pante Macassar]], providing them permanent access to markets, the ferry and airport, even on the rainy season (November to April).<ref name="zeesm" />
