{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}} {{Refimprove|date=September 2015}} {{Infobox Union |name= TUCP |country= The [[Philippines]] |affiliation= [[International Trade Union Confederation|ITUC]] |members= |full_name= Trade Union Congress of the Philippines (TUCP) |native_name= Katipunan ng Manggagawang Pilipino (KMP) |image= [[Image:TUCP logo.png|150px]] |founded= 1975 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Quezon City]], the Philippines |people= Ernesto F. Herrera, PhD, president |website= http://www.tucp.org.ph }}
The '''Trade Union Congress of the Philippines''' (TUCP) is the largest [[national trade union center]] in the [[Philippines]]. Formed in 1975 with the official backing of the [[Ferdinand Marcos|Marcos]] government, TUCP is affiliated with the [[International Confederation of Free Trade Unions]].<ref>[http://www.tucp.org.ph "TUCP,"] TUCP, 2005.</ref>
During the [[1980s]] it was funded with 5,7 millon dollars from the [[United States Congress]] through the [[National Endowment for Democracy]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Branko|last=Marcetic|title=Don't Mourn "Democracy Promotion"|url=https://www.jacobinmag.com/2018/03/trump-national-endowment-democracy-foreign-policy|work=[[Jacobin (magazine)|Jacobin]]|date=March 2018|accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref>
